title: Harris a Zelenski: Hay algunos en mi pa√≠s que podr√≠an obligar a Ucrania a renunciar a gran parte de su territorio - RT
text: La vicepresidenta de EE.UU., Kamala Harris, ha afirmado este jueves en una reuni√≥n con el l√≠der del r√©gimen de Kiev, Vlad√≠mir Zelenski, que hay algunos pol√≠ticos estadounidenses que quieren que Ucrania renuncie a parte de sus territorios. "En mi pa√≠s hay quienes podr√≠an obligar a Ucrania a renunciar a gran parte de su territorio soberano, quienes exigen que Ucrania acepte la neutralidad y exigir√≠an que Ucrania renunciara a las relaciones de seguridad con otras naciones", sostuvo Harris. Seg√∫n la vicepresidenta estadounidense, "no son propuestas de paz", sino "de rendici√≥n, lo cual es peligroso e inaceptable". Esta semana, el candidato republicano a la presidencia de EE.UU., Donald Trump, se√±al√≥ que Ucrania ya no existe y no habr√° suficiente dinero para reconstruirla, incluso si el mundo entero se uniera. "Simplemente no saben qu√© se puede hacer, porque Ucrania ya no existe, ya no es Ucrania. Nunca se podr√°n restaurar esas ciudades y resucitar a los muertos, tantos muertos", subray√≥. Adem√°s, el candidato republicano para la vicepresidencia de EE.UU., J.D. Vance, explic√≥ el plan de Trump para alcanzar una soluci√≥n pac√≠fica, que incluye la creaci√≥n de una zona desmilitarizada a lo largo de la actual l√≠nea de demarcaci√≥n entre Rusia y Ucrania, la negativa de Kiev a unirse a la OTAN y la reconstrucci√≥n de Ucrania financiada por pa√≠ses europeos. ¬ø"Campa√±a a favor" de Harris? Recientemente, el presidente de la C√°mara de Representantes del Congreso de Estados Unidos, Mike Johnson, demand√≥ al Zelenski que destituya a su embajadora en el pa√≠s norteamericano, Oksana Mark√°rova. Mencion√≥ el viaje de Zelenski, organizado por la embajadora, a un sitio de producci√≥n, en una obvia referencia a la planta de municiones en Scranton, Pensilvania, con el que el l√≠der ucraniano comenz√≥ su visita a Estados Unidos el pasado domingo. La misiva de Johnson coincide con el lanzamiento de una investigaci√≥n por el Comit√© de Supervisi√≥n y Rendici√≥n de Cuentas de la C√°mara de Representantes por el uso de recursos que financian los contribuyentes para llevar a Zelenski en avi√≥n a Pensilvania con el objetivo de "hacer campa√±a a favor de la vicepresidenta Kamala Harris de cara a las elecciones presidenciales" de noviembre. - A mediados de junio, el presidente de Rusia, Vlad√≠mir Putin, enumer√≥ las condiciones para comenzar las negociaciones, que contemplan la retirada completa de las tropas de Kiev de los nuevos territorios rusos, as√≠ como su reconocimiento, junto con Crimea y Sebastopol, como sujetos de la Federaci√≥n de Rusia. Paralelamente, debe garantizarse la neutralidad, la no alineaci√≥n, as√≠ como la desnuclearizaci√≥n, la desmilitarizaci√≥n y la desnazificaci√≥n de Ucrania.

author: dpa
title: Bildung: Linke fordert Kindergarten-Moratorium
text:
Bildung Linke fordert Kindergarten-Moratorium
In Th√ºringen sinkt wie in anderen ostdeutschen Bundesl√§ndern die Zahl der Kindergartenkinder. Mancherorts werden schon Einrichtungen geschlossen. Die Linke fordert ein Umsteuern.
Erfurt - Die Th√ºringer Linke-Fraktion hat ein Personal-Moratorium f√ºr Kinderg√§rten gefordert, damit keine Erzieherinnen und Erzieher entlassen werden. ‚ÄûEin Moratorium, wie der Freistaat Sachsen es gemacht hat, dass bis zum 31.12.2026 keine Erzieherinnen entlassen werden‚Äú, sagte die Linke-Bildungspolitikerin Ulrike Grosse-R√∂thig.
Hintergrund sind massiv sinkende Kinderzahlen in den Einrichtungen des Landes aufgrund des demografischen Wandels. In etlichen Kommunen werden Kinderg√§rten geschlossen, teils setzen Tr√§ger Fachkr√§fte bei den Wochenarbeitsstunden herunter.
‚ÄûKein Kindergarten kostet mehr, nur weil weniger Kinder drin sind‚Äú, sagte Grosse-R√∂thig. Nur die Einnahmen aus Elternbeitr√§gen w√ºrden sinken. ‚ÄûUnd da sind wir als Land in der Pflicht.‚Äú
Linke: Kindergarten im Dorf lassen
Die Linke-Fraktion fordert in einem Ma√ünahmen-Papier zur fr√ºhkindlichen Bildung ein ‚ÄûKindergarten-im Dorf-Gesetz‚Äú. Damit sollen Kinderg√§rten erhalten bleiben, auch wenn sie k√ºnftig nicht die geforderte Mindestkinderzahl erreichen. ‚ÄûDazu geh√∂rt, dass Einnahmeausf√§lle durch demografischen Wandel ausgeglichen werden und damit der Kindergarten buchst√§blich im Dorf bleiben kann‚Äú, hei√üt es in dem Papier.
Die stark sinkenden Kinderzahlen sind schon seit l√§ngerem bekannt. Mit einer √Ñnderung des Betreuungsschl√ºssels noch unter der rot-rot-gr√ºnen Minderheitsregierung sollten die Folgen daraus abgemildert und Arbeitspl√§tze in den Einrichtungen gesichert werden.
Eine Erzieherin oder ein Erzieher muss sich nach dem neuen Betreuungsschl√ºssel um weniger Kinder gleichzeitig k√ºmmern als bisher. Die √Ñnderung gilt seit Anfang des Jahres. F√ºr die Umsetzung haben Kommunen eine √úbergangszeit. Nach Angaben des Bildungsministeriums von Ende Mai setzt knapp die H√§lfte der Einrichtungen die neuen Vorgaben um.

author: Casey Young
title: Woman Kicked Out Of Luke Combs Concert For "Dancing Too Hard," Twerking On Security - NewsBreak
text:
By Casey Young ,
7 hours ago
Let the woman dance, dang it. Luke Combs is currently on tour in Australia and he's also been teasing new music over there, so hopefully that means he has some new tunes on the way in addition to announcing more U.S. concert dates . It's actually really neat how many other countries are into country music, and many artists do really well with the international audiences, especially in Europe and Australia. And one fan in particular was clearly having the time of her life at Luke's show in Brisbane at Suncorp Stadium a few days ago. In fact, according to security she was having a little too much fun, because she wound up getting kicked out for "dancing too hard," as reported by The Courier-Mail , an Australian newspaper published in Brisbane. Several vides of her have gone viral on TikTok, where she's seen dancing while Luke's opener Mitchell Tenpenny was on... seriously, she was living her best life. Here's a few different angles: @lily_ballard24 Still didn‚Äôt stop her from having a boogie üòÇ #foryoupage #lukecombs ‚ô¨ Oh No - Kreepa @team_tooney_fishing @Luke Combs was epic but the crowd was a close 2nd! #letthegirldance #sendherhomebuddy #teamtooneyfishing #lukecombsaustraliantour #lukecombs @Mitchell Tenpenny @jordandavis @Lane pitttman @Lily Ballard ‚ô¨ original sound - Team_Tooney_Fishingüá¶üá∫ Well, the woman, named Jolene (seriously, you can't make this stuff up), was also seen jokingly twerking on one of the security people, so I have to imagine that might've been the final straw if they were already considering kicking her out, though it's kind of unclear because she does walk away after doing that. She was escorted out before Combs even went onstage, after being stopped by security after returning from the bathroom... so she didn't even really get to see the concert, which sucks, especially considering how rarely they get big-name country concerts of this caliber over there. KIIS 97.3 breakfast hosts Kip Wightman, Robin Bailey, and Corey Oates spoke with Jolene yesterday, and she says she was just there "having the time of my life," wanting to enjoy the music: "I was literally just having the time of my life. I was dancing to one of my favorite artists, Mitchell Tenpenny, and then supposedly‚Ä¶ the lady in the pink dress behind me had gotten me kicked out‚Ä¶ she obviously didn‚Äôt like my dancing. I was just enjoying myself too much. I didn‚Äôt really care about what was around me. The security guard called me over and said ‚Äòwe‚Äôre really sorry, we‚Äôre going to have to get you to leave.‚Äô And I‚Äôm like, ‚ÄòWhat? Why?‚Äô And they said ‚ÄòThere‚Äôs been a complaint about you dancing and stuff.‚Äô I didn‚Äôt even get to see Luke Combs.‚Äù Bummer... A Suncorp Stadium spokesperson stated that ‚Äúpatrons are not evicted solely for dancing‚Äù: "The patron was engaging in activity that was against the conditions of entry which are designed to allow all fans to enjoy events at the Stadium and so there was no choice but to evict her." Jolene also explained that the stadium "reposted" one of her videos on their Instagram page, though if that's true, it's no longer on there. She added that she "never expected" all of the attention: "They actually reposted my video on that on their on their Instagram page. So it‚Äôs on every platform of social media. It‚Äôs, it‚Äôs crazy hard. I never expected this. Hopefully I can get to Melbourne too!" Jolene hopes to still make it to Luke's show in Sydney, which will take place tomorrow night and Saturday night. Though she clarified that she made sure to get general admission seats this time so she can stand and dance as much as she wants: "I did actually ask them what seats they were, and the lady... said they‚Äôre usually really good seats. And I was like, ‚Äòwell, if possible, GA (general admission) would be great." The Courier-Mail shared Tenpenny's response video, and I have to agree with him in that Jolene was just having a grand old time enjoying country music. I can see how it could be a little annoying to others around her, but they're just sitting there listening and I would think wanting to be there and have fun too. It looks like Jolene had floor seats, which are typically pretty pricey, so I don't blame her for wanting to enjoy the experience as much as possible, again, considering how rarely artists like Combs get over there. Luke, if you're seeing this, get Jolene some tickets in Sydney where she can dance to her hearts content and enjoy the full Luke Combs stadium concert experience. I have no doubt she'll be one of the most enthusiastic fans in the crowd... but yeah, Jolene, maybe refrain from twerking on the security people (though I have to admit, that was the funniest part): Head over to Vivid Seats to grab tickets when Luke Combs is playing near you. They're the only platform that gives you free tickets just for going to concerts, not a bad deal am I right? https://www.instagram.com/couriermail/reel/DFZg5BgPHZK/ Here's the song the unreleased song he teased in Brisbane, "Pushin‚Äô Up Daisies": https://www.instagram.com/p/DFTZ4rdxaU9/ This post contains links from our Affiliate Partners program. If you use these links to make a purchase, we may earn a commission at no additional cost to you. 146

title: NMC nursing graduate Jenkins passes NCLEX-RN | Local News | saipantribune.com
text:
Northern Marianas College 2024 nursing graduate Yi Huang Jenkins has joined the long list of NMC students who have passed the National Council Licensure Examination for Registered Nurses or NCLEX-RN.
Nursing graduates must pass the NCLEX-RN to be able to practice nursing as a Registered Nurse. The exam tests nursing graduates‚Äô knowledge, skills, and abilities to certify that they can apply entry-level nursing practices correctly.
‚ÄúThe college is always incredibly proud to see more NMC nursing graduates pass this exam,‚Äù said NMC president Dr. Galvin Deleon Guerrero. ‚ÄúCongratulations to Yi Huang on successfully passing the NCLEX-RN.‚Äù
‚ÄúWe are so proud of Yi for passing the NCLEX-RN,‚Äù said Nursing Department chair Rosa T. Aldan. ‚ÄúThe Nursing Team is excited for her to begin her career as a registered nurse, joining her peers at the bedside.‚Äù
Jenkins, who graduated from NMC this spring, chose the nursing field for the abundance of opportunities and aspirations she finds in the industry despite its challenges. She attributes much of her determination to her faith. ‚ÄúMy motivation for pursuing nursing is to glorify the Lord by caring for more people in need,‚Äù she said.
When studying for the NCLEX, Jenkins emphasized the importance of time management and effort, stating that they are directly proportional to rewards.
‚ÄúI believe God wants me to become a safe, responsible, and caring nurse,‚Äù Jenkins said. ‚ÄúWhen I was preparing for NCLEX, I studied almost every day from morning to night. This is very difficult because it requires a lot of self-control, patience, and persistence.‚Äù
Akin to her motivation for pursuing her nursing degree with NMC, she stated that her faith was a significant factor in her drive toward obtaining her nursing certification.
Along with the help of the weekly Kaplan sessions, Jenkins highlighted the importance of her NMC nursing instructors, stating that her success is inseparable from their guidance.
She personally credited her skills to her instructors, ‚ÄúI learned how important it is to prioritize my studies through the Nursing Department chair, Mrs. Rosa Aldan. I learned nursing knowledge and gained continuous valuable support from Mr. Johnny Aldan. I learned essential clinical nursing skills from Mrs. Breanna. I learned strict sterile procedures and practical nursing care from Mrs. Tasha. I expanded my knowledge on pediatric care from Dr. Lee. I am also thankful to the administrative assistant, Andrew, for always being there and supporting us whenever we need help.‚Äù
Her advice to NMC students who are planning to take the NCLEX, Jenkins encouraged the prioritization of studying and effort, along with the usage of faith as a form of support. ‚ÄúStudy not only to pass the exam, but also to develop safer clinical skills and practices as a nurse soon,‚Äù she advised.
Jenkins is currently in New Hampshire and looking forward to working in different nursing fields, gaining abundant experiences in local hospitals, and contributing to society. (PR)

title: Sungrow Launches State-of-the-Art 3-Phase Hybrid System in South Africa: A Leap Towards Sustainable Energy
text:
In an era where the quest for sustainable energy solutions has become paramount, Sungrow is setting a new benchmark in South Africa with the launch of its state-of-the-art 3-phase hybrid system. Announced on February 16, 2024, this latest innovation is not just a leap towards cleaner energy; it's a testament to Sungrow's unwavering commitment to safety, efficiency, and customer satisfaction. With a robust 10-year warranty, comprehensive maintenance coverage, and a 24/7 service hotline, Sungrow is poised to revolutionize how homes and businesses in South Africa experience power.
A New Dawn for Renewable Energy
The unveiling of Sungrow's 3-phase hybrid system marks a significant milestone in the renewable energy landscape. Engineered to seamlessly integrate with existing power setups, this system is designed to cater to the dual needs of reliability and sustainability. What sets it apart is not just its ability to deliver clean energy but also its top-notch safety features, smart system integration, and a design so quiet it whispers. Izzat Sankari, Channels Business Director for Sungrow Middle East and Africa, shares the enthusiasm surrounding this launch, "We are thrilled to introduce our cutting-edge 3-phase hybrid system to the South African market. It reflects our dedication to pushing the boundaries of what's possible in renewable energy and our commitment to making clean energy accessible for all."
Unrivaled Quality and Support
The promise of a 10-year warranty on both the inverter and the battery underlines Sungrow's confidence in its product's durability and performance. But it's the full maintenance coverage and the assurance of a 24/7 service hotline that truly underscore the company's focus on customer satisfaction. This holistic approach to product support ensures that businesses and homeowners can make the transition to renewable energy with peace of mind, knowing they are backed by a leader in the industry. "Our aim is not just to sell a product but to provide a seamless, worry-free experience for our customers," Sankari adds.
Leading the Charge Towards Sustainability
Sungrow's launch of the 3-phase hybrid system in South Africa is more than an introduction of a new product; it's a step towards a sustainable future. By prioritizing clean energy, safety, and efficiency, Sungrow is not just leading the charge towards sustainability but is also empowering communities to be part of the renewable energy movement. This initiative not only highlights Sungrow's commitment to environmental stewardship but also its vision for a world where clean energy is within the reach of everyone. As we witness this transformative leap in renewable energy solutions, it's clear that the future is bright, and it's powered by innovations like Sungrow's 3-phase hybrid system.
In conclusion, the launch of Sungrow's 3-phase hybrid system in South Africa represents a pivotal moment in the quest for sustainable energy solutions. With its blend of advanced technology, customer-focused warranty, and support services, Sungrow is not just delivering a product but is paving the way for a cleaner, more sustainable future. As homes and businesses across the country begin to harness the power of clean energy, the impact of this launch will resonate for years to come, marking a significant step forward in the global shift towards renewable energy.

author: Anna Kutz
title: Iowa State Capitol Satanic Temple display: Man takes plea deal | weareiowa.com
text: DES MOINES, Iowa ‚Äî The Mississippi man accused of destroying a Satanic Temple display at the Iowa State Capitol last year took a plea deal Friday in order to have a felony hate crime charge dropped. Former congressional candidate [Michael Cassidy, 35](https://www.weareiowa.com/article/news/crime/iowa-satanic-display-state-capitol-building-vandalism-suspect/524-f3f795f7-aeaa-4d5e-976e-fd6ca57f40a5), vandalized a statue of Baphomet and tore down the temple's display in December 2023. That act earned him one charge of Criminal Mischief in the Third Degree, a Class D felony. On Friday, his attorney filed a guilty plea to an aggravated misdemeanor count of that same charge on his behalf, admitting fault in order to avoid the felony hate crime charge under [Iowa Code 729.A2](https://www.legis.iowa.gov/docs/code/729A.2.pdf). The plea deal results in a deferred judgment for Cassidy with two years probation, an $855 civil penalty and undetermined restitution costs to pay. Local 5 News confirmed the display was built with the state's full permission. [Gov. Kim Reynolds](https://governor.iowa.gov/press-release/2023-12-12/gov-reynolds-statement-satanic-temple-display) called the display "objectionable," while organizers said it was a symbol of their right to religious freedom. Lucien Greaves, co-founder of the [Satanic Temple](https://thesatanictemple.com/), spoke to Local 5 about what the display stands for back in December. "The First Amendment is very important in our ability to be able to identify how we do and coexist peacefully with people while being openly about who we are," Greaves said. "That's why we are often seeking representation in public forums." Cassidy could also be required to participate in a victim-offender dialogue with the temple, if requested.
